otland from English domination. The altered short form <i>Bob</i> is very common, but <i>Hob</i> and <i>Dob</i>, which were common in the Middle Ages and gave rise to surnames, are extinct.  See also  Rupert ."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705191,"age":15,"year":"1315","toYear":"1317","julianDay":2201354,"title":"Famine Strikes Europe","description":"A famine caused by cold winters and wet summers across Europe caused millions to die due to starvation. Desperation from hunger caused high levels of crime, stampedes in bread lines in London, infanticide, and even cannibalism throughout Europe.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705192,"age":28,"year":"1328","julianDay":2206102,"title":"First War of Scottish Independence","description":"The First War of Scottish Independence began after England invaded Scotland in 1296. The Treaty of Edinburgh was signed in 1328 which declared peace between the two kingdoms and brought the war to an end.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705193,"age":37,"year":"1337","toYear":"1453","julianDay":2209390,"title":"The Hundred Years' War","description":"The Hundred Years' War between France and England was largely due to the question of legitimate succession to the French crown.","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When Robert Poutrell was born in 1300, in Nottingham, Nottinghamshire, England, his father, Henry Powtrell, was 34 and his mother, Mrs. Henry Powtrell, was 29. He married Mrs. Robert Poutrell in 1325, in Nottingham, Nottinghamshire, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 2 sons and 1 daughter. He died in 1370, in England, United Kingdom, at the age of 70."},"et":{"1300–1370":"1300–1370","1305–Female":"1305–Surnud","1327–Female":"1327–Surnud","1335–Male":"1335–Surnud","1340–Male":"1340–Surnud","1266–Male":"1266–Surnud","1271–Female":"1271–Surnud","1340":"1340","1370":"1370","1271":"1271","1291":"1291","1327":"1327","1305":"1305","1337":"1337","1315":"1315","1325":"1325","1335":"1335","1300":"1300","14